  "texts": [
    "The report noted that \"little evidence was found of organizations taking strategic approaches to anticipate the impacts of AI on workplaces beyond the intended process or product change\" (p. 2).",
    "With regards to the method used relevant to achieving responsible use of AI in military systems, the initial draft of the score card drew on two frameworks, (i) Australia's AI Ethics Framework (Department of Industry Innovation and Science, 2019; Devitt & Copeland, 2023; Reid et al., 2023) and (ii) the AI Canvas (Agrawal et al., 2018).",
    "A simplified framework was developed with three broad categories (human condition, work safety, and oversight) and three higher-level steps (ideation, development, and application-see Table 13.3).",
    "This new framework was then imbued with principles of good work design considering the physical, cognitive, biomechanical, and psychological characteristics of a A productivity assessment tool designed to improve workflow efficiency is used for penalizing or firing people AI tools to measure human performance are unfairly used to recommend promotions, postings, and awards including medals An AI surveillance tool designed to identify the presence of transient civilians is used to target all humans moving within a target area.",
    "Risk of AI system undermining human capabilities AI system automates processes, assigning workers to undertake remaining tasks resulting in progressive de-skilling Pilots no longer accrue sufficient manual flying hours to respond quickly and competently when an incident occurs."
  ]
}